        "avatar_template": "/user_avatar/forums.foundationdb.org/rishabh/{size}/540_2.png",
        "created_at": "2019-06-03T19:10:32.938Z",
        "cooked": "<p>I had the same doubt. Looks like for storage nodes, Knob \u201cDATA_DISTRIBUTION_FAILURE_REACTION_TIME\u201d used in <a href=\"https://github.com/apple/foundationdb/blob/a4f12a19a3a24bd68676bef8e629d6e855c4702c/fdbserver/DataDistribution.actor.cpp#L2833\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\">storageServerFailureTracker</a> is the timeout for marking a pod healthy/unhealthy. I am not sure if its true for TLog only pod as well, whose failure will also trigger data rebalancing.</p>",
